            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Pending....Damaged. Partially preserved. A cross with dots in the angles marks the beginning of the text. 
 The depiction of the Virgin is directly related to the depiction of Christ on the south pier. Is essentially a dialogue between Virgin and Christ. Virgin the Merciful addresses Christ pleading him to show mercy to the humankind. This representation goes back to the Comnenian art and can be found also in other churches in Cyprus like Panagia tou Arakos at Lagoudera village. </p>
